    • Constructor Detail

      • DataMulti

        public DataMulti(java.lang.String networkID,
         DefaultHeader header,
         org.jboss.netty.buffer.ChannelBuffer buffer)
          throws org.jboss.netty.handler.codec.frame.CorruptedFrameException
        Read the seismic data information from the given ChannelBuffer. This method modifies the ChannelBuffers reader index. The data must be located at the current reader index of the ChannelBuffer.
        Parameters:
        networkID - an ID which is used to generate table names and for earthworm connections.
        header - the header for this packet.
        buffer - the ChannelBuffer that contains the required data.
        Throws:
        org.jboss.netty.handler.codec.frame.CorruptedFrameException - if there are not enough bytes in the ChannelBuffer.
